Jaisalmer, also known as the Golden city is one of the World Heritage sites.
Jaisalmer was founded by Rawal Jaisal.
It was once a thriving trade centre having business relations with Persian countries.
Kuldhara Village located in Jaisalmer is said to be haunted.
Jaisalmer also has one of the largest wind farms in India.
Longewala in Jaisalmer was the battle ground for Indo-Pak war that happened in 1971.

